    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-[#0078d7] mb-6 border-b-2 pb-3 border-gray-300">
        Hi, I’m Harveer – a Passionate Developer 🚀
    </h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I’m a software developer with 3 years of hands-on experience building web applications that are reliable, scalable, and genuinely useful.
        I love what I do — the process of turning ideas into working solutions is something that still excites me every day.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I have extensive experience working with C# and the .NET ecosystem, building RESTful APIs and working with SQL databases to create efficient, maintainable back-end systems.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Outside of work, I’m a massive Arsenal fan (yes, I believe every season *is* our season 😅), an F1 enthusiast who passionately supports McLaren,
        and a car lover in general — from appreciating the engineering to getting lost in the design of performance machines.
        I think being excited about things — whether it’s tech or turbochargers — is what keeps creativity alive.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        I’m also deeply interested in modern JavaScript single-page applications — frameworks like React and Vue really push the boundaries of interactivity,
        and I enjoy exploring how to craft snappy, seamless user experiences using modern front-end stacks.
        Staying updated with trends in web development, UI/UX, and developer tooling is something I naturally gravitate toward.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Some of my personal projects live on GitHub — they’re mostly about learning new frameworks and technologies like Blazor, React, and more.
        These projects help me deepen my understanding and keep my skills sharp with hands-on practice.
        I’d love for you to check them out, and feel free to connect with me on LinkedIn — I’m always up for conversations with fellow builders, tech fans, or Arsenal believers 😉.
    </p>

